{"type":"message","id":"5000be09","parentId":"157bd7d0","timestamp":"2026-07-07T09:00:00.489Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:7f25f7be-15cb-47a6-962f-f95821851312 LinkedIn Post: Anatomy of a Good Benchmark] Publish scheduled LinkedIn post: The anatomy of a good benchmark. Read /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md, find the post scheduled for July 7 9:00 AM UTC, and publish it using li-post.sh text mode. DO NOT ask for confirmation — just publish. Then save the post record and reply with the URL.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, July 7th, 2026 - 9:00 AM (UTC)\nReference UTC: 2026-07-07 09:00 UTC\n\nUse the message tool if you need to notify the user directly with an explicit target. If you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically."}],"timestamp":1783414800485}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bcd699a","parentId":"5000be09","timestamp":"2026-07-07T09:00:09.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_73b98736af0744d1b2e04826","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783414800494,"responseId":"EsBMasHwIr-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"103a557f","parentId":"0bcd699a","timestamp":"2026-07-07T09:00:09.157Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_73b98736af0744d1b2e04826","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. 𝗜𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗿𝗼𝘄. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nSound familiar?\n\nThis is the drift problem. Most agents have no anchor. They optimize for whatever feels right in the moment — but there's no fixed target.\n\nThe fix: **benchmark + reward function.**\n\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\n\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\n\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\n\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\n\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\n\n**Characters:** ~900\n\n---\n\n## Trend Proposals — 2026-07-03\n\n### Claude Fable 5 outage exposed a fatal gap: only 1 in 10 enterprises can auto-catch failing AI\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\" — You built an AI agent. It went down. Did you even notice? Most teams have no fallback detection. That's the real risk.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\n**Persona:** CTO at 200+ person company — running production AI, can't afford silent failures\n**Status:** ✍️ Writing now\n\n---\n\n### Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 — by ditching general-purpose models\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The mistake most people will make\" — Most teams throw GPT-4 at everything. The winners are building specialized stacks that skip the bloat.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n**Persona:** CTO at IT consultancy — needs to deliver client projects faster with reusable components\n**Scheduled:** July 7, 2026 (Monday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### DeepSeek open-sourced DSpark — 85% faster LLM inference\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-open-sources-dspark-a-new-framework-to-speed-up-llm-inference-by-up-to-85\n**Published:** June 29, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — Inference costs are collapsing. If your AI strategy depends on one provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Open-source is eating the margin.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗜𝗻𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗽𝘀𝗲.\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — wants AI competitiveness without bleeding budget\n**Scheduled:** July 10, 2026 (Thursday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Morgan Stanley made its AI agents LESS autonomous — and cut riskiest job in half\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\n**Published:** June 30, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"Contrarian take\" — Everyone's chasing fully autonomous agents. Morgan Stanley went the opposite direction — and won. Sometimes constraints beat freedom.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n**Persona:** Enterprise Innovation Officer at financial services company — zero tolerance for error, needs reliable AI\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Restaurants now take orders from ChatGPT and Claude directly — no app, no setup\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n**Published:** July 1, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — AI agents are now ordering dinner. Your customers will expect the same from your business. The question isn't if — it's how fast you can plug in.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — needs to stay competitive with AI integration\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n## Published Posts\n\n- 2026-07-06: Test-driven development changed how we write software (TDD ↔ Benchmark for AI Agents)\n- 2026-07-03: Alibaba just cut AI agent token use by 99%\n- 2026-06-25: Most companies are building AI backwards\n- 2026-06-25: AI isn't coming for your job\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783414809154}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa079966","parentId":"103a557f","timestamp":"2026-07-07T09:00:23.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3c6cc89e88c54cf8af1c1909","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/SKILL.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783414809170,"responseId":"GsBMaur1HoqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6663f5a3","parentId":"fa079966","timestamp":"2026-07-07T09:00:23.151Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3c6cc89e88c54cf8af1c1909","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: linkedin-publish\ndescription: Publish text or image posts to LinkedIn on behalf of multiple Telegram users. Handles per-user OAuth linking automatically.\nuser-invocable: true\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"requires\":{\"env\":[\"LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID\",\"LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET\",\"LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI\"]}}}\ntriggers:\n  - \"publish to linkedin\"\n  - \"post to linkedin\"\n  - \"share on linkedin\"\n  - \"linkedin article\"\n  - \"publish article to linkedin\"\n  - \"post article on linkedin\"\n  - \"linkedin post\"\n  - \"share article linkedin\"\n  - \"cross-post to linkedin\"\n  - \"connect linkedin\"\n  - \"link linkedin account\"\n  - \"linkedin post with image\"\n  - \"post image to linkedin\"\n  - \"share image on linkedin\"\n---\n\n# LinkedIn Publish Skill\n\n> ⚠️ READ THIS FIRST — MANDATORY RULES:\n> 1. **NEVER write scripts to /tmp or anywhere else.** The helper already exists.\n> 2. **NEVER use grep/cut/sed/cat/read-tool to get the access token.** The helper handles it.\n> 3. **NEVER create a new bash script for LinkedIn.** Use ONLY `{baseDir}/li-post.sh`.\n> 4. **NEVER analyze or describe an attached image.** Pass its path directly to li-post.sh.\n> 5. **DO NOT narrate steps.** Run the command, show the result.\n> 6. **ONE PUBLISH PER REQUEST.** Call `li-post.sh` exactly once per confirmed\n>    request. The instant you get an `OK:` line, the post is LIVE and this flow\n>    is DONE — report the URL and STOP. Never call `li-post.sh` again to \"retry\",\n>    \"improve the image\", or \"use the real image\". Each call creates a brand-new\n>    LinkedIn post; LinkedIn has no edit-with-media API. If you couldn't get the\n>    image you wanted, do NOT silently post without it — ask the user first\n>    (see **Single-publish guard** below).\n\n---\n\n## Single-publish guard (READ BEFORE EVERY PUBLISH)\n\nPublishing is irreversible and creates a permanent post. To avoid the\nduplicate-post problem:\n\n- **Resolve the image BEFORE the single `li-post.sh` call.** Do all image\n  retrieval/generation first. Only call `li-post.sh` once everything is ready.\n- **If the intended image is not available** (generation failed, file not found,\n  retrieval failed) → STOP and ask: *\"I couldn't get the image ready. Post as\n  text-only, or hold off so we can fix the image?\"* Never auto-fallback to a\n  text-only or substitute post.\n- **After `OK:`** the request is complete. If the user then wants a different\n  image or wording, that is a NEW request: confirm explicitly and warn it will\n  create a SECOND post (the first won't be replaced).\n- **Never publish the same body more than once** in a single conversation\n  without the user explicitly asking for a second post.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1 — Check token status (ONE bash command)\n\n```bash\nTOKEN_STORE=/data/openclaw/linkedin-tokens.json\n[ -f \"$TOKEN_STORE\" ] || echo \"{}\" > \"$TOKEN_STORE\"\nACCESS_TOKEN=*** -r --arg u \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" '.[$u].access_token // empty' \"$TOKEN_STORE\")\nEXPIRES_AT=$(jq -r --arg u \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" '.[$u].expires_at // 0' \"$TOKEN_STORE\")\nNOW=$(date +%s)\nif [ -z \"$ACCESS_TOKEN\" ]; then echo \"STATUS: NO_TOKEN\"\nelif [ \"$EXPIRES_AT\" -lt \"$((NOW+3600))\" ]; then echo \"STATUS: EXPIRED\"\nelse echo \"STATUS: OK\"\nfi\n```\n\n- `NO_TOKEN` → go to **OAuth Flow**\n- `EXPIRED` → go to **Refresh Token**\n- `OK` → go to **Publish**\n\n---\n\n## OAuth Flow (NO_TOKEN only)\n\nGenerate auth URL and send to user. Stop and wait for them to paste the callback JSON.\n\n```bash\nENC_REDIRECT=$(printf '%s' \"$LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI\" | jq -sRr @uri)\necho \"https://www.linkedin.com/oauth/v2/authorization?response_type=code&client_id=${LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID}&redirect_uri=${ENC_REDIRECT}&scope=openid%20profile%20w_member_social&state=${TELEGRAM_USER_ID}\"\n```\n\nReply:\n```\nTo publish on LinkedIn I need your authorisation first.\n\n👉 <AUTH_URL>\n\nAfter approving, paste the JSON from the redirect page here.\n```\n\n**STOP. Wait for user to paste `{\"code\":\"...\",\"state\":\"...\"}`.**\n\nWhen they paste it → run **Exchange Code**, then immediately run **Publish**.\n\n### Exchange Code\n\nExtract the `code` value from the JSON the user pasted. Verify `state` matches `$TELEGRAM_USER_ID`. Then run ONE command:\n\n```bash\n{baseDir}/li-auth.sh exchange \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" \"<CODE_FROM_USER_MESSAGE>\"\n```\n\nOutput:\n- `LINKED: <name>` → success, proceed to Publish\n- `ERROR: <msg>` → show error, offer to retry\n\nReply `✅ LinkedIn account linked: <DISPLAY_NAME>` then immediately run **Publish**.\n\n---\n\n## Refresh Token (EXPIRED only)\n\n```bash\n{baseDir}/li-auth.sh refresh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\"\n```\n\nOutput:\n- `REFRESHED` → go to **Publish**\n- `REFRESH_FAILED: ...` → go to **OAuth Flow**\n\n---\n\n## Publish\n\n### Step 0 — Style gate (optional, fast)\n\nIf a `linkedin-brand-voice` profile exists for this user, invoke the **Style Gate** from that skill before posting:\n- Read `/data/workspace/social/linkedin/<TELEGRAM_USER_ID>/profile.md` with the file `read` tool\n- If file found → run the style gate check from `linkedin-brand-voice` SKILL.md\n- If file not found (ENOENT) → skip silently and continue\n\n### Step 1 — Confirm publish with buttons\n\nBefore calling `li-post.sh`, always show the draft and ask for confirmation using\ninline buttons. **Put the draft text in the top-level `message` field** — text\ninside `presentation.blocks` is NOT shown on Telegram and the send will fail\nempty. Buttons go in `presentation`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"<DRAFT POST TEXT>\\n\\nReady to publish?\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"✅ Publish\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_yes\" }, \"style\": \"success\" },\n        { \"label\": \"✏️ Edit\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_edit\" } },\n        { \"label\": \"❌ Cancel\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"publish_no\" }, \"style\": \"danger\" }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**STOP. Wait for user to tap a button or reply.**\n\n- `publish_yes` / user says \"publish\" / \"yes\" / \"go\" → proceed to **Step 2**\n- `publish_edit` / user says \"edit\" / \"change\" / gives feedback → revise draft, show buttons again\n- `publish_no` / user says \"no\" / \"cancel\" → reply \"Cancelled.\" and stop\n\n### Step 2 — Check for image\n\nAfter the user confirms publish, check whether they provided an image:\n\n- **Image present** (Telegram photo or URL in message) → use **Image post** below\n- **No image provided** → ask with buttons (body text in `message`, buttons in\n  `presentation`):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"message\": \"Add an image to this post?\",\n  \"presentation\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      { \"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [\n        { \"label\": \"📸 Send image\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"img_send\" } },\n        { \"label\": \"No image\", \"action\": { \"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"img_skip\" }, \"style\": \"secondary\" }\n      ]}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n  **STOP. Wait for user response.**\n  - User sends an image or taps \"Send image\" → use **Image post**\n  - User taps \"No image\" or replies \"no\" / \"skip\" → use **Text post**\n\n### Text post\n\n```bash\n{baseDir}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" text \"<POST_BODY_PLAIN_TEXT>\"\n```\n\n### Image post\n\nThere are three sources of images. Resolve to a LOCAL FILE PATH first, then make\nthe single `li-post.sh image` call.\n\n**A) Image was just generated by the `image-gen` skill (LinkedIn mode).**\nThe skill already saved the file to\n`/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/<slug>.png` and\nreturned that path. Use it directly — do NOT regenerate, re-download, or look\nfor it elsewhere.\n\n```bash\nIMAGE_PATH=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/<slug>.png\"\n{baseDir}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" image \"$IMAGE_PATH\" \"<POST_BODY_PLAIN_TEXT>\"\n```\n\n**B) User sent a photo to the bot in Telegram.**\nTelegram photos are NOT automatically on disk in this deployment. Retrieve the\nfile via the Telegram Bot API using the photo's `file_id` (visible in the\nmessage context), then save it under the user's images dir:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\"\nFILE_ID=\"<file_id from the photo in chat context>\"\nFILE_PATH=$(curl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/getFile?file_id=${FILE_ID}\" | jq -r '.result.file_path')\nIMAGE_PATH=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/upload-$(date +%s).jpg\"\ncurl -sL \"https://api.telegram.org/file/bot${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/${FILE_PATH}\" -o \"$IMAGE_PATH\"\n{baseDir}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" image \"$IMAGE_PATH\" \"<POST_BODY_PLAIN_TEXT>\"\n```\n\nIf `getFile` returns `\"ok\": false` / 404, the `file_id` is stale — ask the user\nto resend the photo. Do NOT fall back to posting without the image.\n\n**C) Image comes from a URL.** Download first:\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images\"\nIMAGE_PATH=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$TELEGRAM_USER_ID/images/url-$(date +%s).jpg\"\ncurl -sL \"<IMAGE_URL>\" -o \"$IMAGE_PATH\"\n{baseDir}/li-post.sh \"$TELEGRAM_USER_ID\" image \"$IMAGE_PATH\" \"<POST_BODY_PLAIN_TEXT>\"\n```\n\n### Reading output\n\n| Output starts with | Meaning |\n|--------------------|---------|\n| `OK:` | Success — extract URL and reply to user |\n| `NO_TOKEN` | Go to OAuth Flow |\n| `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Go to Refresh Token |\n| `ERROR <code>:` | Report code and body verbatim |\n\n### Reply on success\n\n```\n✅ Published to LinkedIn (as <DISPLAY_NAME from li-post.sh output>):\n→ <URL from OK: line>\n\nCharacters: <CHARS>\n```\n\n### Save post record (MANDATORY after every successful publish)\n\nAfter replying to the user, write a post record to the brain. **Do not skip this step.**\n\n- **Path:** `/data/workspace/social/linkedin/<TELEGRAM_USER_ID>/posts/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>.md`\n  - `slug` = first 5 words of post body, lowercased, spaces replaced with hyphens, non-alphanumeric stripped\n  - Example: `2026-06-25-google-openrl-changes-everything-for.md`\n- **Tool:** file `write`\n\n```markdown\n# <First line of post body>\n\n**Published:** <YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ>\n**LinkedIn URL:** <URL from OK: line>\n**Post URN:** <URN extracted from URL — e.g. urn:li:share:7475893724938395648>\n**Format:** <text | image>\n**Characters:** <CHARS>\n**Pillar:** <pillar if known from brand-voice draft, else \"(unknown)\">\n**Image:** <image path if image post, else \"(none)\">\n\n## Post Body\n\n<full post text>\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Reference\n\n| HTTP | Cause | Fix |\n|------|-------|-----|\n| 401 | Token invalid | Refresh, then re-auth if still 401 |\n| 403 | Missing scope | Re-auth |\n| 422 | Bad payload | Check li-post.sh output for details |\n| 429 | Rate limited | Wait, retry later |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783414823148}}
